The initial state of this code was downloaded from

https://sourceforge.net/projects/logsurfer/

which indicates a BSD license.

The code itself doesn't indicate a license but does indicate that one is free to distribute
source or binaries. It appears to be silent on the issue of distributing changes, though
perhaps distributing patches would be OK.

The same version (1.8) is available as a source RPM with the following spec file contents:

#
# spec file for package logsurfer (Version 1.5a)
#
# Copyright (c) 2002 SuSE Linux AG, Nuernberg, Germany.
# This file and all modifications and additions to the pristine
# package are under the same license as the package itself.
#
# please send bugfixes or comments to feedback@suse.de.
#


Name:           logsurfer
Version:        1.8
Release:        8%{?dist}
# License:        X11/MIT     # this was the old license, not sure if just MIT is right
# See BNC 779005 - unresolved license issue.  Must be resolved prior to factory submission
License:        MIT

Terry's website (https://www.crypt.gen.nz/logsurfer/) says nothing about license.


